-- Greece's NBG eyeing tapping markets with share offering
-- By George Georgiopoulos
-- Sat Apr 12, 2014 10:56AM EDT
-- None



ATHENS, April 12 (Reuters) - Greece's largest lender National Bank (NBG) <NBGr.AT> is considering tapping international markets with a share offering as part of plans to plug a capital shortfall, a senior executive at the bank told Reuters on Saturday.

"All solutions are being reviewed in the present circumstances, without excluding an equity offering," the banker said, declining to be named.